Various fixes to the run-talos script

* Use the virtualenv via bin/activate (prevent sillies with subprocesses)
* Kill all bcontroller subprocesses when we start/stop (hack around the
fact that bcontroller inappropriately uses threading until we rebase
on mozprocess)
Updates to various things to make the basic animation test work

Add support for a "startAnimation" handler inside content

This will let us start animating from talos, which is useful to get the
timing right.

Add a cheesey firefox extension that can send/receive events via jsbridge

We'll use this to start/stop video capture as needed

First iteration of a new eideticker superproject

Instead of just creating a python module for video capture, we'll include my
branch of talos as a submodule and use it directly. This should make setup
and prototyping faster.
the eideticker

Make eideticker an installable package

Currently we "install" the eideticker server as a script, you must manually
create a "captures" directory for it to dump its data into. For our initial
use-case, it looks like it will be easier to control the capturing directly
from the test harness, so I'll probably be removing the server for now
shortly.

MonkeyRunner devicecontroller should print READY when, well, ready

Helps us determine that it's ready to start up

First draft of an eideticker dashboard

Not entirely sure if this strictly should be in the Eideticker repo, but it's
easier to put it in here for now.

Trim captures, image files to capture area before writing to disk

We no longer store all the background information which we don't care about as
part of the capture process. This decreases the size of the captures (and
their videos), making it more feasible to upload videos as part of the
forthcoming Eideticker dashboard.

Misc. additions changes to controller/runtest program

Most important is ability to specify name of capture file, which we'll use
for automation

Modify clock canvas test to use devicecontroller (just to make test last 5 secs)

Gives more predictable results.
Make sure we can connect to HTTP server before opening

Better checkerboarding handling, checkerboard on "magenta" colour not pattern

Trying to detect a checkerboard pattern was just too difficult. Note this
requires a patched version of Fennec which checkerboards to the background
color, and obviously the background color for a page must be set to magenta.
Fix up capture-test program to account for recent changes

Fix up checkerboarding scroll test to help with synchronization issues

We now grab the current frame number from the video capture program, and use
that to account for the start/end of a capture. Helps to remove redundant
capture information from start/end (though there still seem to be some issues).

Allow synthesizing native events inside tests via monkeyrunner

Also add a scrolling demo, based on taskjs.org, which demonstrates this.
